<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>9460</id>
    <title>Breaking change: stream.publish with action link doesn t update status</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">According to the docs_ calling Stream.publish without  attachments  should update a user s status.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">As of approximately April 2nd_ statuses aren t updated if Stream.publish is called with action links_ even if there are no attachments.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">This is a breaking change and is causing users of our application (Status Shuffle_ app ID 8109791468) to complain non-stop.</sentence>
            <sentence id="3.2">We re one of the largest apps on the platform which means we ve been getting hundreds of complaints about this every day :(</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">I can only hope someone can look into this before our application suffers irreparable damage.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">To reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="5.2">$actionLinks = array( array( text  =&gt;  test _   href  =&gt;  http://www.example.com )); 
$res = $facebook-&gt;api_client-&gt;stream_publish( hello _ null /* attachment */_ $actionLinks_ null /* to */_ $uid);</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">Expected:
User s status should be set to  hello  (i.e.  hello  should appear near the user s name on the profile page)</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="7">
            <sentence id="7.1">Actual:
Only a feed entry is created.</sentence>
            <sentence id="7.2">The status remains unchanged.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
